tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Played on PGA TOUR Canada and made five cuts in 11 starts. Recorded one top-25 finish...Finished T11 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December. Was denied a top-10 finish and even better status when Matt Fast birdied the final two holes of the tournament to pass him.

2013: Missed the cut at the John Deere Classic.

2012: Finished T18 at the South Georgia Classic, his only made cut in three starts on the Web.com Tour. 

2011: Struggled on the Web.com Tour and made only one cut in 11 starts during the year. 

2010: Played 23 Web.com Tour events,made 15 cuts and had four top-25 finishes. Had two T12 performances, at the Melwood Prince George's County Open and Soboba Golf Classic. Ended the year No. 82 on the money list. 

2009: Missed the cut at the Soboba Golf Classic on the Web.com Tour...Finished 14th on the Gateway Tour money list. 

2008: Did not make the 36-hole cut at the Xerox Classic in Rochester, N.Y...Placed fifth on the Gateway Tour money list. 

2006: Earned two starts on the PGA TOUR, at the Washington, D.C.-area Booz Allen Classic and the U.S. Bank Championship in Milwaukee. Missed the cut in both. Also missed the cut in his only Web.com Tour stop, at the Miccosukee Championship. 

2001: First career PGA TOUR start came at the Honda Classic, where he missed the 36-hole cut.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Named the 1998 Big West Conference Player of the Year.
tourBios.personal: Attended Silver Lake Regional High School in Kingston, Mass...Has two sisters...Twitter account is @justindpeters...Has worked as a telemarketer and at a car dealership...Says "You don't choose golf, golf chooses you."...If he was playing golf he'd be a professional poker player...Favorite courses are the Olympic Club and Hualalaii and he'd like play Augusta National...Has a Woody Woodpecker cell phone ringer...Likes to watch the TV show "Shark Tank" and the movie "The Natural"...Hawaii is a favorite vacation spot...Would put Woody Austin, Fred Couples and poker champ Phil Ivey in his dream foursome...Winner of the inaugural Golf Channel's "Big Break"...Favorite entertainer is Criss Angel, and athlete is Roger Federer.

tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Finished T26 at Canada's Q-School with rounds of 72-68-78-70. Make five cuts in 11 starts with his season-best finish a T23 at the Bayview Place Island Savings Open.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T35th at the Brasil Champions presented by Embrase.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T51st in Total Eagles on the Web.com Tour.
